{"title":"arts_sixth_week","date":"2019-11-10T10:24:47.000Z","link":"2019/11/10/arts-sixth-week","tags":["arts"],"updated":"2019-11-10T12:07:14.699Z","content":"<h1 id=\"A\">A<a href=\"2019/11/10/arts-sixth-week#A\"></a></h1><p>题：<a href=\"https://leetcode-cn.com/problems/climbing-stairs/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">climbing stairs</a><br>解：<a href=\"https://github.com/youguanxinqing/RoadOfDSA/blob/master/LeetCode/070/climbing_stairs_1.go\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">climbing_stairs_1.go(迭代)</a>, <a href=\"https://github.com/youguanxinqing/RoadOfDSA/blob/master/LeetCode/070/climbing_stairs_2.go\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">climbing_stairs_2.go(递归+缓存)</a></p>\n<h1 id=\"R\">R<a href=\"2019/11/10/arts-sixth-week#R\"></a></h1><p><a href=\"https://uxdesign.cc/designing-at-google-10-things-i-know-to-be-true-e033d97e5f13\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Designing at Google: 10 things I know to be true</a></p>\n<p>不妨将这篇文章取个别名：职场中你需要知道的那些事儿。</p>\n<p>作者在里边说了蛮多事儿的，比如设计应该针对所有人，尽早发现问题，关注你的强项……我最印象深刻的是：投资自己。在这一段中，有句话我又极为赞同：<strong>To become the best version of yourself, embrace the uncomfortable.</strong> </p>\n<p>不管如何，我认为敢于跳出舒适圈的人必然优秀于常人，尽管这些人并不都能获得世俗眼里的成功。但又怎样呢？他们自有一脉坚毅的精神传递给后人，等时机成熟，后人们一鸣惊人、一飞冲天。</p>\n<h1 id=\"T\">T<a href=\"2019/11/10/arts-sixth-week#T\"></a></h1><p>公司要我临时起一个 web 服务器，要看演示效果，难不成我还要给他搞个 supervisor ? 当然万万不可能！</p>\n<p>因此这里推荐 tmux。tmux 的 session 概念真的很香，又不占我终端控制权，又维持着命令行服务，能够很轻易地 ctrl-c 进程。管理起来还是蛮方便的。</p>\n<h1 id=\"S\">S<a href=\"2019/11/10/arts-sixth-week#S\"></a></h1><p><a href=\"http://louiszhai.github.io/2017/09/30/tmux/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Tmux 使用手册</a></p>\n","prev":{"title":"arts_seventh_week","link":"2020/01/10/arts-seventh-week"},"next":{"title":"arts_fifth_week","link":"2019/11/03/arts-fifth-week"},"plink":"http://yoursite.com/2019/11/10/arts-sixth-week/","toc":[{"title":"A","id":"A","index":"1"},{"title":"R","id":"R","index":"2"},{"title":"T","id":"T","index":"3"},{"title":"S","id":"S","index":"4"}]}